Convalescent sera collected from animals exposed to BoCV strains from clade 2, subgroup A, could not be used to differentiate viruses from clades 1 and 2. (Fig. 2
) The error bars in Fig. 2 represent standard error of the mean. In contrast, convalescent sera collected from animals exposed to BoCV strains from clade 2, subgroups B and C, did have a statistically significant (P
 < 0.05) greater neutralizing power for strains from clade 2 as opposed to one strain from clade 1. There was no statistically significant difference between neutralization of any of the clade 2 subgroups using any of the sera evaluated.
